# FlowDoors Design System Rules

## Core Principles

When implementing designs, always reference:

- docs/redesign/ for mockups and guides
- Use FlowDoors colors: #00aeef (blue), #8dc63f (green), #2e2e2e (charcoal)
- Follow Next.js 15 and TypeScript best practices
- Use Tailwind CSS for styling
- Make all components mobile responsive (test at 320px, 768px, 1024px)

## Brand Colors

Primary Blue: #00aeef (FlowDoors Blue)

- Use for: Primary CTAs, links, active states, focus rings
- Hover: #0097d1
- Light: rgba(0, 174, 239, 0.1)

Success Green: #8dc63f (FlowDoors Green)

- Use for: Success states, positive indicators, trust badges
- Hover: #7ab82f
- Light: rgba(141, 198, 63, 0.1)

Charcoal: #2e2e2e (FlowDoors Charcoal)

- Use for: Primary text, headings, important content
- Never use pure black (#000000)

## Component Guidelines

- All buttons should have hover and focus states
- Use consistent spacing: 8px, 16px, 24px, 32px, 48px
- Border radius: 8px (inputs), 12px (cards), 16px (large cards)
- Shadows: 0 2px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.05) for subtle, 0 4px 16px rgba(0,0,0,0.1) for prominent
- Font sizes: 48px (hero numbers), 24px (section headers), 16px (body), 14px (small), 12px (tiny)

