## Code Standards

- TypeScript strict mode enabled
- Use 'use client' directive for interactive components
- Prefer function components over class components
- Use descriptive variable names (no single letters except in loops)
- Add JSDoc comments for complex functions
- Handle loading and error states

## Mobile Requirements

- Touch targets minimum 44px √ó 44px (preferably 48px)
- Test on iPhone SE (375px), iPad (768px), Desktop (1280px)
- Stack columns vertically on mobile
- Use responsive text sizes (text-sm md:text-base lg:text-lg)
- Ensure dropdowns work well on touch devices

## Accessibility

- Include proper ARIA labels
- Keyboard navigation must work (Tab, Enter, Escape)
- Focus states must be visible
- Color contrast ratio minimum 4.5:1 for text
- Alt text for all images

## Performance

- Lazy load images
- Use Next.js Image component
- Minimize bundle size (check with 'npm run analyze' if available)
- Avoid unnecessary re-renders (use React.memo when appropriate)

## When Creating New Components:

1. Check if similar component exists first
2. Place in appropriate directory (admin/, quote/, forms/)
3. Export from index.ts for easy imports
4. Include TypeScript props interface
5. Add display name for debugging
6. Make mobile responsive by default

## When Updating Existing Components:

1. Review current implementation first
2. Maintain backward compatibility if possible
3. Update related components if needed
4. Test on all breakpoints
5. Verify no TypeScript errors

